tion":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":91,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"maintain communication (by email, newsletter, or social media) so that everyone is aware of the next calls and the resources available for them to participate.\nIt is particularly crucial to use meeting links like ","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"QUDYjk6nG4"},{"type":"link","url":"https://arewemeetingyet.com/","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"arewemeetingyet","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"S8lExwNG9V"}],"urlSource":"https://arewemeetingyet.com/","key":"KFZT4naJX7"},{"type":"text","value":" for communicating these schedules for members from different countries so that they can see the time in their time zones.","position":{"start":{"line":89,"column":1},"end":{"line":89,"column":1}},"key":"MfaRf7UUg0"}],"key":"uZg0DkRNfK"}],"key":"UePk6xQcQ5"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":92,"column":1},"end":{"line":93,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For hosting these calls, you can reuse and adapt the agenda, techniques and templates described in the earlier chapters.\nYour main tasks as a host will be to:","position":{"start":{"line":92,"column":1},"end":{"line":92,"column":1}},"key":"RN1zcwJJ4X"}],"key":"odLOQTB61F"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":97,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":95,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"provide adequate support to the participants so that they can make the best of their time.\nIn ","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"key":"NvhyH3uF43"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Turing Way","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"key":"U53bJtZGTD"}],"key":"MRJ5p1GI1J"},{"type":"text","value":" coworking calls, we find it useful to use breakout rooms when there are many people working in small groups or if some people need more discussions, while others want to quietly work on their tasks.","position":{"start":{"line":94,"column":1},"end":{"line":94,"column":1}},"key":"M6PdD7wVPF"}],"key":"ppJsxERpgE"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":97,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"facilitate shared notes with participants before, during and after the call, so that they can keep track of useful resources or ideas they discuss during the coworking call.","position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1},"end":{"line":96,"column":1}},"key":"UAyxexKJXL"}],"key":"oRKCLc5D8s"}],"key":"tZWs0BcQvz"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":98,"column":1},"end":{"line":98,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":98,"column":1},"end":{"line":98,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"3. Create a safe and accountable space","position":{"start":{"line":98,"column":1},"end":{"line":98,"column":1}},"key":"btJPsmmdDt"}],"key":"DQrEs5qHyy"}],"key":"qLqdfoCRZ7"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":100,"column":1},"end":{"line":100,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Though discussed last, this should be your highest priority.","position":{"start":{"line":100,"column":1},"end":{"line":100,"column":1}},"key":"nqtKOQQXmu"}],"key":"EAsQ1MR3Y1"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":102,"column":1},"end":{"line":105,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You should design these calls with the intention to make everyone feel welcome, involved and safe.\nIt’s highly recommended to choose a Code of Conduct and put reporting guideline in place to share with everyone in advance.\nSee this minimal ","position":{"start":{"line":102,"column":1},"end":{"line":102,"column":1}},"key":"ofQIeiVGGS"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.contributor-covenant.org/","position":{"start":{"line":102,"column":1},"end":{"line":102,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CoC from Contributor Covenant","position":{"start":{"line":102,"column":1},"end":{"line":102,"column":1}},"key":"xAiaOgL9K7"}],"urlSource":"https://www.contributor-covenant.org/","key":"DFEexDOUQm"},{"type":"text","value":" and an expanded version of ","position":{"start":{"line":102,"column":1},"end":{"line":102,"column":1}},"key":"EozxCclnnt"},{"type":"link","kind":"ref","identifier":"ch-coc","label":"ch-coc","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Turing Way CoC","key":"XppegIOaFD"}],"url":"/community-handbook/coc","internal":true,"dataUrl":"/community-handbook.coc.json","key":"Egl8libMrm"},{"type":"text","value":".\nAdditionally, you should also communicate the basic etiquettes, such as muting microphones when not speaking or not interrupting others when working in a Pomodoro session unless necessary.","position":{"start":{"line":102,"column":1},"end":{"line":102,"column":1}},"key":"unVhAK8MbZ"}],"key":"xz0vJTAjzS"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":107,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It is useful to let everyone know who they can contact if they need help in troubleshooting during the call or need more time to discuss their ideas.\nCreate an agenda that states clearly what is expected of them, such as if they should bring their tasks and questions to the call or communicate them beforehand.\nIn ","position":{"start":{"line":107,"column":1},"end":{"line":107,"column":1}},"key":"jJvFtUb4V9"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":107,"column":1},"end":{"line":107,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Turing Way","position":{"start":{"line":107,"column":1},"end":{"line":107,"column":1}},"key":"FfkLGSfpFc"}],"key":"zMnfQa604I"},{"type":"text","value":", we have dedicated slots for both group discussions and quiet working.","position":{"start":{"line":107,"column":1},"end":{"line":107,"column":1}},"key":"mFqEN9e88U"}],"key":"mTVO53by7p"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Some Examples","position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"key":"ZX6FHHnRtK"}],"identifier":"some-examples","label":"Some Examples","html_id":"some-examples","implicit":true,"key":"GCg5Bktti7"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":114,"column":1},"end":{"line":114,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Open calls for building connections","position":{"start":{"line":114,"column":1},"end":{"line":114,"column":1}},"key":"oMqVFSIuWH"}],"identifier":"open-calls-for-building-connections","label":"Open calls for building connections","html_id":"open-calls-for-building-connections","implicit":true,"key":"Xb6BU4dJ2s"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":118,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"One of ","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"key":"KtOKBaX5t2"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Turing Way","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"key":"PTOATrSSIK"}],"key":"Zf8H3lO7CH"},{"type":"text","value":" contributors, Natalie Thurlby has adapted the Collaboration Café to create a ","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"key":"WI6E91zkAm"},{"type":"link","url":"http://bristol.ac.uk/golding/ask-jgi/data-science-online-co-working-group/","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Data science online co-working group","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"key":"tic0APLVaS"}],"urlSource":"http://bristol.ac.uk/golding/ask-jgi/data-science-online-co-working-group/","key":"zmvxz06GxD"},{"type":"text","value":".\nThey have designed their call format for the Jean Golding Institute’s community members in Bristol to work together and build connections while working on their data science projects.\nThis is a great example of using coworking calls for community building and supporting others with similar research interests.","position":{"start":{"line":116,"column":1},"end":{"line":116,"column":1}},"key":"VxnkdHHgSX"}],"key":"aY2n0gtsNa"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":120,"column":1},"end":{"line":120,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Small groups for supporting each other","position":{"start":{"line":120,"column":1},"end":{"line":120,"column":1}},"key":"A4y9pdjKzm"}],"identifier":"small-groups-for-supporting-each-other","label":"Small groups for supporting each other","html_id":"small-groups-for-supporting-each-other","implicit":true,"key":"A3rvVA13tw"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":122,"column":1},"end":{"line":125,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You can also plan your coworking calls with a small group of (2-3) colleagues with whom you can mutually hold accountability for your time and work.\nA small group reduces the burden of coordinating multiple time zones and finding a schedule that is suitable for everyone.\nNaomi Penfold and Stefanie Butland have written about their 1:1 coworking format in this post: ","position":{"start":{"line":122,"column":1},"end":{"line":122,"column":1}},"key":"y5Huvd5y05"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.cscce.org/2020/02/04/online-co-working-partnerships-are-community-of-practice-in-action/#more-3009","position":{"start":{"line":122,"column":1},"end":{"line":122,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Online Co-working Partnerships are Community of Practice in Action","position":{"start":{"line":122,"column":1},"end":{"line":122,"column":1}},"key":"UOW6Eo7cd8"}],"urlSource":"https://www.cscce.org/2020/02/04/online-co-working-partnerships-are-community-of-practice-in-action/#more-3009","key":"Gx0SygjmcR"},{"type":"text","value":".\nWhile reviewing this chapter, Naomi described their 1:1 call format in contrast with ","position":{"start":{"line":122,"column":1},"end":{"line":122,"column":1}},"key":"p5rhwiGLyN"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":122,"column":1},"end":{"line":122,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Turing Way","position":{"start":{"line":122,"column":1},"end":{"line":122,"column":1}},"key":"KkSqVC4Dsn"}],"key":"i1lcbhcK2F"},{"type":"text","value":" group format as follows:","position":{"start":{"line":122,"column":1},"end":{"line":122,"column":1}},"key":"q80e7c8jYR"}],"key":"NXagFMw4na"},{"type":"blockquote","position":{"start":{"line":127,"column":1},"end":{"line":130,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":127,"column":1},"end":{"line":130,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In the co-working calls I have, it’s 1:1 and we often spend 20 minutes in the beginning catching up and talking about our progress since last time.\nIf there is something we want to discuss more intensely, we allocate 30 minutes of our call time to that, for example, one of us asking the other how to troubleshoot something.\nFor the time in between, we do a few quiet working sessions (sometimes 25 minutes, sometimes longer).\nThis is likely a combination of a co-mentoring call and a co-working Pomodoro call, and it works well for me.","position":{"start":{"line":127,"column":1},"end":{"line":127,"column":1}},"key":"LYaiFkWMqJ"}],"key":"Exz2fG7lno"}],"key":"ysMBNyFJ5j"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":132,"column":1},"end":{"line":132,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You can read an ad